    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-02-19T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-02-19T02:00:00-05:00" n="622"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d622">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/2676: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-02-19T16:00:00+09:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 19, 1920—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>58. Your no. 32, February 2, 4 p.m.<note n="88" xml:id="d622fn88">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_624">p. 624</ref>.</note> I am
                    assured by the Foreign Office that the report of a proposed loan by Okura and
                    Company to the Chinese Government is utterly without foundation. All my
                    investigations confirm this statement of the Foreign Office.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
